egory:2010s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s British animated television series]]\n[[Category:2018 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2018 British television series debuts]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American flash animated television series]]\n[[Category:American preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:American television programs based on children's books]]\n[[Category:American television series with live action and animation]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about children]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about siblings]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about families]]\n[[Category:British children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:British children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:British flash animated television series]]\n[[Category:British preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:British television programmes based on children's books]]\n[[Category:British television series with live action and animation]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:PBS Kids shows]]\n[[Category:PBS original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by WGBH]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Animated children\u2019s TV series}}{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| genre                    = [[Children's television series]]\n| show_name                = Pinkalicious & Peterrific\n| image                    = Pinkalicious & Peterrific.jpg\n| image_size               = \n| runtime                  = approx. 30 minutes\n| based_on                 = {{Based on|''[[Pinkalicious]]''|Victoria and Elizabeth Kann}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Belinda Ward\n| opentheme                = \"It's a Pink Feeling\"\n| endtheme                 = \"It's a Pink Feeling\" (instrumental)\n| director                 = \n| developer                = \n| executive_producer       = {{Plain list|\n* Dorothea Gillim\n* Victoria Kann\n}}\n| producer                 = [[WGBH-TV|WGBH Boston]]\n| location                 = \n| company                  = {{Plain list|\n* [[Sixteen South]]\n* [[WGBH Educational Foundation]]\n}}\n| presenter                = \n| starring                 = \n| voices                   = {{Plain list|\n* Kayla Erickson\n* Jaden Waldman\n* Molly Lloyd\n* Jayce Bartok\n* Echo Picone\n}}\n| country                  = {{Plain list|\n* United Kingdom\n* United States\n}}\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 2\n| num_episodes             = 39<!-- Update only after a new episode airs -->\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| network                  = [[PBS Kids]]\n| picture_format           = \n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{start date|2018|02|19}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| followed_by              = \n| related                  = \n}}\n'''''Pinkalicious & Peterrific''''' is a British-American [[education]]al [[animated]] [[children's television series]] based on the ''[[Pinkalicious]]'' books by Victoria Kann and Elizabeth Kann. The program premiered on [[PBS Kids]] on February 19, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://dandelionmoms.com/2017/05/pinkalicious-peterrific-is-coming-to-pbs-kids-next-february/ |title=Pinkalicious & Peterrific is coming to PBS Kids next February! |publisher=Dandelionmoms.com |date=May 18, 2017 |accessdate=September 25, 2017}}</ref> [[WGBH-TV|WGBH]] and [[Sixteen South]] produced 38 episodes for the first season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/business/news/cartoon-has-belfast-studio-in-the-pink-35779639.html |title=Cartoon has Belfast studio in the pink |work=[[Belfast Telegraph]] |date=June 2, 2017 |accessdate=September 26, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://woub.org/2017/05/18/pbs-kids-announces-new-series-pinkalicious-peterrific-premiering-february-19-2018/ |title=PBS Kids Announces New Series Pinkalicious & Peterrific, Premiering February 19, 2018  |publisher=[[WOUB-TV|WOUB]] |date=May 18, 2017 |accessdate=September 25, 2017}}</ref> A second and third season have been ordered, with the second season premiering in March 2020.<ref name=\"CPB 2019\">{{cite web | title=PBS KIDS and WGBH Boston Announce Season 2 and 3 of PINKALICIOUS & PETERRIFIC | website=CPB | date=2019-10-04 | url=https://www.cpb.org/pressroom/PBS-KIDS-and-WGBH-Boston-Announce-Season-2-and-3-PINKALICIOUS-PETERRIFIC | access-date=2019-10-12}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nDesigned to encourage preschool-age children to explore [[the arts]] and develop their creativity, the series follows Pinkalicious and her brother Peter as they imagine how the world looks through her artful eye. Each episode includes two 11 minute stories and live action shorts.\n\n==Voice cast==\n* Kayla Erickson<ref name=\"deadline\"/> as Pinkalicious Pinkerton. She is an imaginative young girl who loves the color pink more than any other color, as well as soccer, painting, tinkering, and using her creativity. She is the show's main character.\n* Jaden Waldman as Peter Pinkerton,<ref>https://twitter.com/PinkaPeterPBS/status/966418004362764288</ref> Pinkalicious' younger brother.<ref name=\"deadline\"/> He likes riding his scooter, playing with blocks, and tagging along on Pinkalicious' adventures. He has some angst over being the youngest, as evidenced in \"No Honking\" in his song, \"Music to Me\".{{fact|date=May 2018}}\n* Molly Lloyd as Mrs. Pinkerton (Mom). She likes to invent.{{fact|date=May 2018}}\n* Jayce Bartok as Mr. Pinkerton (Dad).<ref>{{cite episode |title=Gnome More Nonsense |series={{PAGENAME}} |author=Jasmine |quote=Hi, Mr. Pinkerton!}}</ref><ref name=\"plant episode\">{{cite episode |series=Pinkalicious |title=Plantastically Pink}}{{unreliable source?|reason=no minute mark given to check claims|date=August 2019}}</ref> He likes to give advice to Pinkalicious and Peter.\n* Echo Picone as Kendra Klee,<ref name=\"plant episode\"/> Pinkalicious' friend.<ref name=\"deadline\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/pinkalicious-peterrific-pbs-kids-series-victoria-mann-1202243974/|title=\u2018Pinkalicious & Peterrific\u2019 Toon Based On Book Series Coming To PBS Kids \u2013 TCA|first=Erik|last=Pedersen|date=January 16, 2018|website=deadline.com|accessdate=March 2, 2018 |quote= Pinkalicious finds creative opportunities everywhere she looks, with Peter and her friends Jasmine, Rafael and Kendra in tow}}</ref> She has straight shoulder-length black hair and wears dark clothing. Her favorite color is black and she does not like pink. She often makes sarcastic comments towards others, but usually{{when|date=May 2018}} comes through in the end and goes along with Pinkalicious' ideas.\n* Daia Johnson as Jasmine Cooper,<ref name=\"plant episode\"/> Pinkalicious and Peter's friend.<ref name=\"about announce\"/> She has curly black hair in [[bunches]] held by yellow ribbons. She likes the color yellow, as well as playing the recorder. \n* Raleigh Shuck as Lila Goodway,<ref name=\"plant episode\"/> Pinkalicious and Peter's friend.<ref name=\"about announce\"/> She has brown hair [[braid]]ed in twintails, dresses in purple, and plays soccer. She is a member of Pinkalicious' clique, but isn't seen hanging out with them often due to her shy nature. She is sensitive, as shown in \"Slumber Party\", where she misses her mom at the eponymous party, and in \"Peter's Blues\", where she gets discouraged after Peter sings about her missing the net in soccer.\n* Justice Quirez as Rafael Martinez,<ref name=\"plant episode\"/> Pinkalicious and Peter's friend.<ref name=\"about announce\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pbs.org/about/blogs/news/pbs-kids-announces-new-series-pinkalicious-peterrific-premiering-february-19-2018/|title=PBS KIDS Announces New Series PINKALICIOUS & PETERRIFIC,  Premiering February 19, 2018 |author=|date=|website=PBS.org|accessdate=March 2, 2018 |quote=Kids will simply connect with the great characters Pinkalicious and Peter, and their friends Jasmine, Rafael and Lila}}</ref> His mother is Mayor Martinez.<ref>https://twitter.com/PinkaPeterPBS/status/969724042319187971</ref> He has a dog named Rusty. He likes to paint. Even though he and Pinkalicious don't always agree, they're still friends.\n* Nicole Ruiz as Frida Martinez, Peter's friend and Rafael's younger sister.\n* [[Rebecca Soler]] as Mayor Martinez, the mayor of Pinkville and Rafael's mom. She is a drama queen, crying over a broken pencil in \"Peter's Blues\".\n*Blanca Camacho as Mrs. Plum and Ezra Knight as Mr. Plum, they have a poodle named Pinky who Pinkalicious puppy-sat, and Pinkalicious has encountered them on the sidewalk in multiple episodes.\n* [[Marlo Thomas]] as Gertie,<ref>https://collider.com/collider-kids-our-exclusive-clip-reveals-pbs-kids-new-series-pinkalicious-peterrific</ref> Lila's stuffed pink dragon<ref>https://twitter.com/PinkaPeterPBS/status/974706871780200450</ref>\n* Erin Fritch as Ms. Penny.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.imdb.com/name/nm1029506/filmotype/actress|title=Erin Fritch|website=IMDb|language=en|access-date=2018-05-31}}</ref>\n<!-- NEED NOTABILITY\nBrittany Johnson as Penelope and Garbage Woman\n? as Goldie (unicorn).\n? as shoe salesman\nChuck Lewkowicz as Norman (garden gnome)\n-->\n\n==Episodes==\n===Season 1 (2018\u201319)===\n{{Episode table|background=#FFC0CB|total_width=90|overall=|season=|title=|airdate=|prodcode=|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 1\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n|Title           = Fairy House/Pinkabotta & Peterbotta\n|RTitle          = <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ket.org/episode/PIPE%20%20000101|title=Fairy House/Pinkabotta & Peterbotta|publisher=[[Kentucky Educational Television|KET]]|accessdate=January 30, 2018}}</ref>\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|2|20}}\n|ProdCode        = 101\n|LineColor       = FFC0CB\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNu